description: This is a methodological framework to model Cultural Ecosystem Services at large scales. It is composed by an Artificial Intelligence and a Machine Learning model.

End-to-end machine learning pipeline for synthetic SNP data. Includes data simulation, preprocessing, model training (Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost), evaluation metrics, and visualizations. Ethical, reproducible framework for genomic prediction research.

AI Passport delivers cryptographic passports for machine learning models, enabling the tamper-proof verification of AI outputs. This project represents a major advancement in AI governance, providing a critical framework for tracking AI threats and validating the authenticity of harmful content to ensure greater safety and transparency.

MOA is an open source framework for Big Data stream mining. It includes a collection of machine learning algorithms (classification, regression, clustering, outlier detection, concept drift detection and recommender systems) and tools for evaluation.

AI-driven discovery of Metal Organic Frameworks (MOFs) for efficient CO capture from cement plants and catalytic conversion into methanol using solar energy. Includes datasets, preprocessing scripts, machine learning models, and analysis notebooks.

Application Deployment and Description  To deploy the application, I used Streamlit, a Python-based framework designed for rapid development of interactive data science and machine learning applications. Streamlit allows users to input data through a web interface and obtain real-time predictions along with explanations.
A machine learning project built with Swift and Apples Natural Language framework to perform real-time sentiment analysis on user input.
A Rust machine learning framework.

Developed within the framework of the Machine Learning curriculum at Ben-Gurion University, this project translates theoretical algorithmic concepts into a practical, end-to-end data processing pipeline.
A step-by-step framework for a supervised machine learning project focused on image classification, using a Cat vs. Dog problem as an example with HOG and LBP features extraction
Modeltime unlocks time series forecast models and machine learning in one framework

Temporal machine learning framework for early sepsis risk prediction based on multivariate ICU time-series data, leveraging a stacked (LSTM) architecture. Beyond retrospective evaluation, the model was deployed within a lightweight mobile application, enabling real-time inference, and visualization of short-term risk trajectories.
Causal machine learning framework for pharmacovigilance signal detection in electronic health records: Drug-induced acute kidney injury

This repository contains an ongoing project focused on detecting payment delays and banking fraud using Artificial Intelligence. The goal is to build a robust, end-to-end machine learning pipeline capable of identifying anomalous patterns in loan repayments, transaction behaviors, and potential fraudulent activities within financial systems.

brpc is an Industrial-grade RPC framework using C++ Language, which is often used in high performance system such as Search, Storage, Machine learning, Advertisement, Recommendation etc. "brpc" means "better RPC".
In this project, we use machine learning framework Graph Neural Network-based Simulators (GNS) as a surrogate model to predict stress in granular flow.

This repository contains a complete, end-to-end research framework for understanding how monetary liquidity regimes shape equity valuations, factor returns, and market dynamics. The project combines macro-finance theory, econometric modeling, and modern machine learning methods to build a structural interpretation of liquidity-driven markets.

Physics-informed and data-driven modeling framework for hydrogen production from fermentation-derived industrial wastewaters via supercritical water gasification (SCWG), integrating thermodynamic simulations, machine learning surrogate models, hybrid batch reactor dynamics, uncertainty quantification, and sensitivity analysis.
Autoware-ML is a machine learning framework for multiple tasks, supporting the full lifecycle - training, evaluation, optimization, and deployment of models with native runtime support in Autoware.
A Comprehensive Performance Analysis System for Homomorphic Encryption Libraries

FedEasy is an intuitive powerful yet simple to use Federated Learning framework. Our goal is to streamline the process of setting up and running federated learning experiments with ease, making advanced machine learning techniques accessible to researchers and developers alike.
Code of the publication: Integrated Genome-Wide Association Study and Machine Learning Approach For Characterization of Biofilm Formation Determinants in Staphylococcus aureus
This repo is for manuscript of "Adaptive Machine Learning Framework for Debris Flow Monitoring in Nonstationary Environments in Illgraben, Switzerland", which is under review.
A machine learning framework template project for SUFE HPC.
ML + bioinformatics project for breast cancer subtype classification and biomarker discovery

This project proposes a predictive data-driven framework to forecast restaurant health inspection scores and identify establishments at higher risk of violations using machine learning models using the San Francisco Health Inspection Scores (2024-current) dataset as a baseline
This repository provides a unified framework for building efficient, lightweight, and deployment-ready deep learning models.
Building a simple deep learning framework and some machine learning/deep learning models from scratch (pure Numpy and Pytorch)

SAFER-6G : Framework IA pour la scurit des rseaux 6G. Le projet utilise le Machine Learning pour analyser le trafic rseau simul, dtecter les cyberattaques en temps rel (dbit, latence, etc.), et prsenter les alertes sur un tableau de bord interactif.
Transformers: the model-definition framework for state-of-the-art machine learning models in text, vision, audio, and multimodal models, for both inference and training.
Open-source machine learning framework developed by Google for building and training neural networks and other AI models.

LEO CDP is an open-source, AI-first Customer Data Platform for building customizable, self-hosted, privacy-friendly CDP infrastructure. It unifies data collection, enables real-time analytics, audience segmentation, and personalized marketing  powered by big data and machine learning.

A machine learning framework for detecting phishing URLs using multiple classifiers (MDC, Bayes, k-NN, SVM). Implements feature selection, dimensionality reduction, and class balancing techniques to improve accuracy and generalization.
A framework that uses preprocessing and multiple machine learning models to collect data and predict economic crises for countries around the world.
Machine learning framework for Enterococcus cecorum pathogenicity prediction (Antimicrobial Resistance + genomic islands + pangenome)
Predict football match outcomes using the W-5 Multi-Agent AI Consensus Framework, achieving high accuracy with a blend of AI and machine learning techniques.

Equitrain: A Unified Framework for Training and Fine-tuning Machine Learning Interatomic Potentials
A Machine Learning Framework for Agricultural  Decision Support

Security Vulnerability Detection Framework designed to identify and mitigate key operating system vulnerabilities such as buffer overflows, cache poisoning, and abnormal system behavior. The framework combines rule-based monitoring with machine learningbased anomaly detection to provide real-time alerts and improved system security

This project contains a set of **Jupyter notebooks** to help students and data scientists deeply understand and visualize the *four main classification metrics* used in machine learning: **Accuracy, Precision, Recall, and F1 Score**.

Accent Converter is an AIpowered Django web application that processes audio files, performs accent conversion using machine learning models, and generates bilingual subtitles. It combines speech processing, transliteration, and a scalable backend with a simple, interactive frontend for accessibility.
A full-stack web application that predicts stock prices using historical data and machine learning. Built with Django REST Framework for the backend and React for the frontend.

OpenCSE is a modular Computational Science & Engineering research framework for coupling parallel numerical PDE solvers with Scientific Machine Learning models. It supports GPU-accelerated simulation, neural surrogate modeling, and physics-informed learning, exposed through a web-based experiment management system for reproducible CSE research.
Building machine learning algorithms from the ground up using Python. No frameworksjust pure implementations to understand the fundamentals.
Capstone project implementing an AI-driven Zero Trust Security Framework using machine learning and virtualized environments

This repository provides a machine learning framework that integrates structural and coevolutionary features to classify mutations as compensatory, offering insights into evolutionary adaptation and protein stability
Sum-of-Gaussians Neural Network (SOG-Net) is a lightweight and versatile framework for integrating long-range interactions into machine learning force field.
A performant and dynamic MachineLearning framework written in .NET
Polars-native automatic machine learning feature generation framework.

PredNetRSA is a machine learning-based framework for predicting network performance by estimating RSA (Routing and Spectrum Allocation) metrics. It leverages data-driven models to forecast key performance indicators, enabling efficient network optimization and resource management in optical and communication networks.
Thesis project on phishing detection using Machine Learning
Interpretable Machine Learning Framework for Designing High Ionic Conductivity in Low-Temperature Lithium-Ion Battery Electrolytes
Site criado utilizando o framework do MKDocs com o template do professor Humberto Sandmann, da ESPM. Contm os projetos do semestre para a disciplina de Machine Learning.
Enhancing Malignant Transformation Predictions in Oral Potentially Malignant Disorders: A Novel Machine Learning Framework Using Real-World Data

This project presents a data-driven framework designed to optimise healthcare resource allocation across Chinese prefecture-level cities using advanced predictive analytics and machine learning techniques. Healthcare resource allocation has become increasingly complex due to growing populations, regional inequalities, and dynamic healthcare demands

gold-random-forest-trading-system ist ein modulares Quant-Framework fr algorithmisches Gold-Trading. Es verbindet Machine Learning, technische Analyse, Sentiment, Backtesting und Live-Trading ber die Oanda API. Ziel ist die Untersuchung, ob sich der Goldpreis unter realistischen Marktbedingungen zuverlssig prognostizieren lsst.
Research implementation of W-5 Multi-Agent AI Consensus Framework for football match outcome prediction | AI-powered sports analytics using LLMs + Machine Learning | 85.9% accuracy

A fast, distributed, high performance gradient boosting (GBT, GBDT, GBRT, GBM or MART) framework based on decision tree algorithms, used for ranking, classification and many other machine learning tasks.
A Julia machine learning framework

Decentralized Federated Learning (DFL) framework with blockchain consensus, secure aggregation, P2P communication, and post-quantum identity verification. A scalable, privacy-first solution for distributed machine learning across edge devices, healthcare, finance, and IoT networks.

This project presents a complete end-to-end analytics framework developed for Blinkit, using 8,523 real transactional records to generate actionable business insights through data preprocessing, exploratory analysis, machine learning, and interactive dashboarding.
Codebase for Bates Physics Department thesis: PeakMap: A Two-Stage Machine Learning Framework for Methane Peak Detection.

CRATe (Chimeric RNAs of All Types) is a machine learning framework integrating foundation models and Positive-Unlabeled (P-U) learning to identify both canonical and noncanonical chimRNAs without relying on genome annotations or splice signals.

Advanced NLP and LLM-based framework for analyzing Sri Lankan Reddit discussions: combining data collection, machine learning, deep learning, and transformer models to extract thematic, sentiment, and policy insights.
An inference server for your machine learning models, including support for multiple frameworks, multi-model serving and more
A unified framework for machine learning with time series

With the help of machine learning models, automated AI systems, and big data frameworks, the researchers build models for processing vast datasets in real-time to enhance the accuracy and speed of astronomical discoveries.
A full-stack website built using the React and FastAPI frameworks, utilizing machine learning to recommend comics based on previous ratings.
Tech Soft 3D tutorials of python CAD framework for machine learning development. Requires HOOPS AI

Hefei-NAMD-S is a predictive framework constructed based on a machine learning stacking model.   The framework is designed to efficiently generate the input files required by the Hefei-NAMD package (NATXT and EIGTXT), thereby driving the non-adiabatic molecular dynamics simulation process.

This repository contains the implementation of a hybrid physics-machine learning framework for autonomous pH adjustment in complex buffered systems. The system combines Theoretical Titration Curve Generation modeling with active learning to enable rapid, precise pH optimization using low-cost automated hardware.

This is my final year project where I use machine learning to predict the binding success rate between drug molecules and protein targets. I will code the frontend off of the react framework and use a REST API to connect it to the backend - Neural network, Database

This project proposes a computational, data-driven diagnostic framework for Alzheimers disease (AD) by integrating microbiome-derived genome-scale metabolic models (GEMs) and machine learning to accurately predict disease stages from gut microbial activity.
A lightweight, feature-engineered machine learning framework (FEIIDS) for real-time IoT intrusion detection, ensuring high accuracy and low computational cost.

Open-source machine learning framework for Java. Designed with speed and lightweight in mind.

Lightweight devops framework on top of Kubernetes & Terraform (OpenTofu) which simplifies cloud-native deployment to the same complexity level as Docker Compose. Ideal for demo's and proof-of-concepts in AI, machine learning pipelines and RAG. Works locally on Minikube and on Azure cloud by production pushing. Can pull images, but does not do CI/CD

The Multi-Agent RLRM (Reinforcement Learning with Reward Machines) Framework is a library designed to facilitate the formulation of multi-agent problems and solve them through reinforcement learning. The framework supports the integration of Reward Machines (RMs), providing a modular and flexible structure for defining complex tasks.

Tywra ML is a front-end machine learning website built using the React.js library and the Next.js framework. This website was created as a simple project while also continuing advanced learning of JavaScript.

Machine-learningbased analytical framework for identifying anomalous Medicare Part D prescribing patterns using publicly available federal datasets. Developed as an independent research and analytics contribution.
A pure Rust implementation of TensorFlow, providing a full-featured machine learning framework with Rust's safety and performance.

Machine learning framework for urban flood probability prediction using meteorological, topographic, and hydrologic features. Achieves R = 0.861 with Neural Networks. CSE 572 Final Project, Arizona State University.

"A comprehensive repository on Big Data Analytics showcasing scalable data processing, distributed computing, and advanced analytical techniques. Includes examples, tools, and frameworks for handling massive datasets, enabling insights through Hadoop, Spark, machine learning, and visualization."
An automated machine learning (AutoML) framework that uses Genetic Algorithms (GAs) to efficiently select the optimal ML algorithm and hyperparameters for a given dataset.
Testing the machine learning framework GFlowNet for the directed studies course at Carleton University
Applying AI for early ADHD and autism screening through a sociotechnical framework combining neuroscience, ethics, and data science.

A real-time Sign Language Detector using computer vision techniques, particularly hand gesture recognition. The system leverages OpenCV for image processing and python-based machine learning frameworks, to recognize hand gestures and translate them into readable text. MediaPipe is used to efficiently track hand movements.
